{%- comment -%}
  ============================================================
  CART PROGRESS BAR COMPONENT
  ============================================================

  Purpose:
  Displays a tiered progress bar inside the shopping cart that
  motivates customers to increase their order value by showing
  how close they are to unlocking rewards:
    - Tier 1: Free shipping (default threshold: €39.99)
    - Tier 2: Free gift product (default threshold: €99.99)

  How to use:
  Drop this file into your Shopify theme's "sections" folder,
  then include it in your cart template (cart.liquid or cart drawer).
  All thresholds and the gift product are configurable via the
  Shopify Theme Editor — no code changes needed.

  Tech stack: Liquid (server-side) + CSS + JavaScript (client-side)
  ============================================================
{%- endcomment -%}


{%- comment -%}
  ============================================================
  SECTION 1: LIQUID LOGIC (Server-Side Rendering)
  ============================================================
  This runs on Shopify's server before the page is sent to the
  browser. It reads the current cart value and calculates which
  state to show on initial page load.

  Why server-side first?
  - Ensures the correct state is visible immediately (no flash
    of wrong content while JS loads)
  - Works even if JavaScript fails to load
  - SEO and accessibility friendly
  ============================================================
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- liquid

  comment
    --------------------------------------------------------
    STEP 1: Read thresholds from Theme Settings
    --------------------------------------------------------
    The theme editor stores values in euros (e.g. 39.99), but
    Shopify's cart.items_subtotal_price is in CENTS (e.g. 3999).
    So we multiply the settings by 100 to convert euros → cents.
    This keeps all math in the same unit and avoids rounding errors.
  endcomment
  assign shipping_threshold = section.settings.free_shipping_threshold | times: 100
  assign gift_threshold = section.settings.free_gift_threshold | times: 100
  assign gift_variant_id = section.settings.free_gift_variant_id

  comment
    --------------------------------------------------------
    STEP 2: Get the current cart subtotal
    --------------------------------------------------------
    items_subtotal_price = total of all product prices in cart.
    It excludes shipping and taxes — which is what we want,
    because we're measuring "how much product have you added?"
  endcomment
  assign cart_total = cart.items_subtotal_price

  comment
    --------------------------------------------------------
    STEP 3: Calculate progress bar state
    --------------------------------------------------------
    We use a CONTINUOUS progress model:
      - 0% to 50%   = progress toward free shipping
      - 50% to 100% = progress toward free gift

    Why continuous? If we measured each tier independently
    (0-100% per tier), the bar would SHRINK when crossing
    the first threshold — confusing for the customer.
    With continuous progress, the bar only ever grows.

    Three possible states:
      1. cart < shipping threshold  → working toward free shipping
      2. cart >= shipping but < gift → shipping unlocked, working toward gift
      3. cart >= gift threshold     → all rewards unlocked!
  endcomment

  if cart_total >= gift_threshold
    comment STATE 3: Both rewards unlocked endcomment
    assign progress = 100
    assign status_text = 'Sie erhalten ein Geschenk & Versand kostenlos!'
    assign helper_text = ''
    assign bar_state = 'complete'

  elsif cart_total >= shipping_threshold
    comment STATE 2: Shipping free, working toward gift endcomment
    assign gift_range = gift_threshold | minus: shipping_threshold
    assign gift_progress = cart_total | minus: shipping_threshold | times: 50 | divided_by: gift_range
    assign progress = 50 | plus: gift_progress
    assign remaining_cents = gift_threshold | minus: cart_total
    assign remaining = remaining_cents | money_without_trailing_zeros
    assign status_text = 'Kostenloses Geschenk ab ' | append: gift_threshold | divided_by: 100.0 | money
    assign helper_text = 'Noch ' | append: remaining | append: ' bis zum kostenlosen Geschenk'
    assign bar_state = 'active'

  else
    comment STATE 1: Working toward free shipping endcomment
    assign progress = cart_total | times: 50 | divided_by: shipping_threshold
    assign remaining_cents = shipping_threshold | minus: cart_total
    assign remaining = remaining_cents | money_without_trailing_zeros
    assign status_text = 'Kostenloser Versand ab ' | append: shipping_threshold | divided_by: 100.0 | money
    assign helper_text = 'Noch ' | append: remaining | append: ' bis zum kostenlosen Versand'
    assign bar_state = 'active'

  endif
-%}


{%- comment -%}
  ============================================================
  SECTION 2: HTML MARKUP
  ============================================================
  The progress bar structure with three parts:
    1. Status text (above the bar) — tells the customer the current goal
    2. The bar itself — visual fill showing progress
    3. Helper text (below the bar) — shows remaining amount

  Data attributes (data-*) pass threshold values to JavaScript
  so the JS can recalculate when the cart updates dynamically.

  Accessibility:
    - role="progressbar" tells screen readers this is a progress indicator
    - aria-valuenow/min/max provide the numeric progress to assistive tech
    - aria-label gives a human-readable description of the current state
  ============================================================
{%- endcomment -%}

<div class="cart-progress"
     data-section-id="{{ section.id }}"
     data-shipping-threshold="{{ shipping_threshold }}"
     data-gift-threshold="{{ gift_threshold }}"
     data-gift-variant-id="{{ gift_variant_id }}"
     role="progressbar"
     aria-valuenow="{{ progress }}"
     aria-valuemin="0"
     aria-valuemax="100"
     aria-label="{{ status_text }}">

  {%- comment -%} Status text: shows current goal or success message {%- endcomment -%}
  <p class="cart-progress__status{% if bar_state == 'complete' %} cart-progress__status--success{% endif %}">
    {{ status_text }}
  </p>

  {%- comment -%} Progress track: gray background with colored fill {%- endcomment -%}
  <div class="cart-progress__track">
    <div class="cart-progress__fill{% if bar_state == 'complete' %} cart-progress__fill--complete{% endif %}"
         style="width: {{ progress | at_most: 100 }}%">
    </div>
  </div>

  {%- comment -%} Helper text: shows "Noch X€ bis zum..." (hidden when all rewards unlocked) {%- endcomment -%}
  {%- if helper_text != blank -%}
    <p class="cart-progress__helper">{{ helper_text }}</p>
  {%- endif -%}
</div>


{%- comment -%}
  ============================================================
  SECTION 3: CSS STYLES
  ============================================================
  Scoped styles for the progress bar component.

  Design tokens (from the case study spec):
    - Navy blue (#002F6C): progress bar fill + status text
    - Green (#4A9500): success state (all rewards unlocked)
    - Light gray (#F0F4F6): component background
    - Gray (#6b6d70): helper text

  The fill bar uses a cubic-bezier transition for a smooth,
  slightly elastic animation when the width changes.
  ============================================================
{%- endcomment -%}

<style>
  /* Component wrapper — the rounded card that holds everything */
  .cart-progress {
    background: #F0F4F6;
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 14px 16px;
    margin: 16px 0;
    transition: background 0.4s ease;
  }

  /* When all rewards are unlocked, background turns light green */
  .cart-progress.is-complete {
    background: #e8f5e0;
  }

  /* Status text above the bar (e.g., "Kostenloser Versand ab 39,99€") */
  .cart-progress__status {
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: #002F6C;
    margin: 0 0 10px;
    transition: color 0.4s ease;
  }

  /* Success state: status text turns green */
  .cart-progress__status--success {
    color: #4A9500;
  }

  /* The gray track (background of the bar) */
  .cart-progress__track {
    height: 7px;
    background: #d0d8de;
    border-radius: 4px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  /* The navy blue fill that grows as cart value increases */
  .cart-progress__fill {
    height: 100%;
    background: #002F6C;
    border-radius: 4px;
    /* Smooth animation when width changes — cubic-bezier gives a slight ease-out feel */
    transition: width 0.5s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);
  }

  /* Success state: fill turns green */
  .cart-progress__fill--complete {
    background: #4A9500;
  }

  /* Helper text below the bar (e.g., "Noch 10,00€ bis zum kostenlosen Versand") */
  .cart-progress__helper {
    font-size: 12px;
    color: #6b6d70;
    margin: 8px 0 0;
  }
</style>


{%- comment -%}
  ============================================================
  SECTION 4: JAVASCRIPT (Client-Side Dynamic Updates)
  ============================================================
  The Liquid code above handles the INITIAL page load. But when
  a customer adds/removes items without a full page reload (AJAX
  cart updates), we need JavaScript to recalculate and re-render
  the progress bar in real-time.

  This script also handles the FREE GIFT logic:
    - When cart crosses the gift threshold → auto-add gift product
    - When cart drops below the threshold → auto-remove gift product

  Everything is wrapped in an IIFE (Immediately Invoked Function
  Expression) to avoid polluting the global scope.
  ============================================================
{%- endcomment -%}

<script>
  (function() {
    /* --------------------------------------------------------
       SETUP: Find the component and read configuration
       --------------------------------------------------------
       We read the threshold values from the HTML data attributes.
       These were set by Liquid from the Theme Settings, so the
       JS and Liquid always use the same values automatically.
    */
    const el = document.querySelector('.cart-progress');
    if (!el) return; /* Safety check: exit if component not found */

    const SHIPPING = parseInt(el.dataset.shippingThreshold, 10); /* e.g. 3999 (cents) */
    const GIFT = parseInt(el.dataset.giftThreshold, 10);         /* e.g. 9999 (cents) */
    const GIFT_VARIANT = el.dataset.giftVariantId;               /* Shopify variant ID */

    let debounceTimer; /* Used to prevent rapid-fire updates */

    /* --------------------------------------------------------
       HELPER: Format cents into German euro string
       --------------------------------------------------------
       Converts 3999 → "39,99€" using German locale formatting.
       German uses comma for decimals (39,99) not dot (39.99).
    */
    function formatMoney(cents) {
      return (cents / 100).toLocaleString('de-DE', {
        minimumFractionDigits: 2,
        maximumFractionDigits: 2
      }) + '\u20AC';
    }

    /* --------------------------------------------------------
       SHOPIFY CART API: Fetch current cart state
       --------------------------------------------------------
       Shopify provides a JSON endpoint at /cart.json that returns
       the full cart contents including items and subtotal.
    */
    async function getCart() {
      const res = await fetch('/cart.json');
      return res.json();
    }

    /* --------------------------------------------------------
       SHOPIFY CART API: Add the free gift product
       --------------------------------------------------------
       Uses /cart/add.js to add the gift variant with quantity 1.
       This is called automatically when the cart crosses the
       gift threshold.
    */
    async function addGift() {
      await fetch('/cart/add.js', {
        method: 'POST',
        headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
        body: JSON.stringify({ items: [{ id: GIFT_VARIANT, quantity: 1 }] })
      });
    }

    /* --------------------------------------------------------
       SHOPIFY CART API: Remove the free gift product
       --------------------------------------------------------
       Uses /cart/change.js to set the gift line item quantity to 0.
       Note: Shopify line items are 1-indexed (first item = line 1).
       This is called when the cart drops below the gift threshold.
    */
    async function removeGift(lineIndex) {
      await fetch('/cart/change.js', {
        method: 'POST',
        headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
        body: JSON.stringify({ line: lineIndex, quantity: 0 })
      });
    }

    /* --------------------------------------------------------
       MAIN UPDATE FUNCTION
       --------------------------------------------------------
       Called whenever the cart changes. Does three things:
       1. Checks if gift should be added/removed
       2. Recalculates the progress bar percentage
       3. Updates all DOM elements with new values
    */
    async function update() {
      const cart = await getCart();
      const total = cart.items_subtotal_price;
      const hasGift = cart.items.some(i => String(i.variant_id) === GIFT_VARIANT);

      /* --- Gift auto-management ---
         If cart is above gift threshold and gift isn't in cart → add it.
         If cart dropped below threshold but gift is still in cart → remove it.
         After adding/removing, we call update() again to recalculate with
         the new cart state. */
      if (total >= GIFT && !hasGift) {
        await addGift();
        return update();
      } else if (total < GIFT && hasGift) {
        const idx = cart.items.findIndex(i => String(i.variant_id) === GIFT_VARIANT);
        if (idx !== -1) {
          await removeGift(idx + 1); /* +1 because Shopify lines are 1-indexed */
          return update();
        }
      }

      /* --- Calculate progress (continuous model: 0-50% shipping, 50-100% gift) --- */
      let progress, statusText, helperText, isComplete;

      if (total >= GIFT) {
        /* STATE 3: All rewards unlocked */
        progress = 100;
        statusText = 'Sie erhalten ein Geschenk & Versand kostenlos!';
        helperText = '';
        isComplete = true;
      } else if (total >= SHIPPING) {
        /* STATE 2: Shipping free, progressing toward gift (bar: 50%-100%) */
        const giftProgress = (total - SHIPPING) / (GIFT - SHIPPING);
        progress = 50 + (giftProgress * 50);
        statusText = 'Kostenloses Geschenk ab ' + formatMoney(GIFT);
        helperText = 'Noch ' + formatMoney(GIFT - total) + ' bis zum kostenlosen Geschenk';
        isComplete = false;
      } else {
        /* STATE 1: Progressing toward free shipping (bar: 0%-50%) */
        progress = (total / SHIPPING) * 50;
        statusText = 'Kostenloser Versand ab ' + formatMoney(SHIPPING);
        helperText = 'Noch ' + formatMoney(SHIPPING - total) + ' bis zum kostenlosen Versand';
        isComplete = false;
      }

      /* --- Update the DOM --- */
      const fill = el.querySelector('.cart-progress__fill');
      const status = el.querySelector('.cart-progress__status');
      const helper = el.querySelector('.cart-progress__helper');

      fill.style.width = progress + '%';
      fill.classList.toggle('cart-progress__fill--complete', isComplete);
      status.textContent = statusText;
      status.classList.toggle('cart-progress__status--success', isComplete);
      el.classList.toggle('is-complete', isComplete);

      /* Update accessibility attributes so screen readers announce the change */
      el.setAttribute('aria-valuenow', Math.round(progress));
      el.setAttribute('aria-label', statusText);

      if (helper) {
        helper.textContent = helperText;
        helper.style.display = helperText ? '' : 'none';
      }
    }

    /* --------------------------------------------------------
       EVENT LISTENERS: Trigger updates when cart changes
       --------------------------------------------------------
       Two strategies to catch cart changes:

       1. 'cart:change' custom event — modern Shopify themes
          emit this event when the cart is modified via AJAX.

       2. Form submit interception — catches traditional form-based
          cart updates (add to cart buttons, quantity changes).

       Both are debounced (150-300ms delay) to prevent multiple
       rapid-fire updates if the customer clicks quickly.
    */
    document.addEventListener('cart:change', function() {
      clearTimeout(debounceTimer);
      debounceTimer = setTimeout(update, 150);
    });

    document.querySelectorAll('form[action="/cart"]').forEach(form => {
      form.addEventListener('submit', function() {
        setTimeout(() => {
          clearTimeout(debounceTimer);
          debounceTimer = setTimeout(update, 300);
        }, 200);
      });
    });
  })();
</script>


{%- comment -%}
  ============================================================
  SECTION 5: SHOPIFY THEME SETTINGS SCHEMA
  ============================================================
  This {% schema %} block tells Shopify's Theme Editor what
  settings to show for this section. Store managers can change
  the thresholds and gift product directly in the Theme Editor
  without touching any code.

  Settings:
    1. free_shipping_threshold — cart value needed for free shipping
    2. free_gift_threshold — cart value needed for the free gift
    3. free_gift_variant_id — which product variant to auto-add as gift
       (found in Shopify Admin → Products → Variants)
  ============================================================
{%- endcomment -%}

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Cart Progress Bar",
  "settings": [
    {
      "type": "number",
      "id": "free_shipping_threshold",
      "label": "Free Shipping Threshold (€)",
      "default": 39.99,
      "info": "Cart value needed for free shipping"
    },
    {
      "type": "number",
      "id": "free_gift_threshold",
      "label": "Free Gift Threshold (€)",
      "default": 99.99,
      "info": "Cart value needed for a free gift"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "free_gift_variant_id",
      "label": "Gift Product Variant ID",
      "info": "The variant ID of the free gift product"
    }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}
